Hi!
Will be great to use sass_processor in settings to specify styles which are used for some setup CMS. 
For example I need configure some setting to use style on each pages, like this:
`ARCTIC_COMMON_MEDIA_ASSETS = {
    'css': {
        'all': sass_processor('styles/global.scss'),
    }
}`
But I can''t do this because I have the error "django.core.exceptions.ImproperlyConfigured" ...
And I found the solution to use django lazy function;

`def lazy_load_global_sass():
    """Lazy load sass_processor after settings ware configured"""
    from sass_processor.processor import sass_processor
    return sass_processor('styles/global.scss')

ARCTIC_COMMON_MEDIA_ASSETS = {
    'css': {
        'all': (lazy(lazy_load_global_sass, str)(),)
    }
}`
BUT, when i want to compile scss offline,  'compilescss' command skip global.scss file,
because **FuncCallVisitor** can't count the lazy function calls to register this file to compile.

So, I suggest if it will be possible to create settings option where register the specific scss files to compile.

